OL,5,Crow
OL,7,F"However, policy must be set by
OL,8,Fparliamentarians, who answer to the
OL,9,Fpeople.
OL,11,F"Government and Parliament have a
OL,12,Flegitimate role in setting the
OL,13,Fsentencing framework. It is right that
OL,14,Fwe now have greater democratic and
OL,15,Fjudicial oversight of the direction of
OL,16,Fthe Council's work and the final
OL,17,Fguidelines they publish."
